HEADWORD: Myroxylon
<hw>My*rox"y*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>my`ron</grk> a sweet juice distilling from a plant +
<grk>xy`lon</grk> wood.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
leguminous trees of tropical America, the different species of which
yield balsamic products, among which are balsam of Peru, and balsam of
Tolu. The species were formerly referred to
<gen>Myrospermum</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

